d in classical ballet, on stage, film, and television.\nAmong his numerous stage productions were On the Town, Peter Pan, High Button Shoes, The King and I, The Pajama Game,  Bells Are Ringing, West Side Story, Gypsy, and Fiddler on the Roof. Robbins was a five-time Tony Award-winner and a recipient of the Kennedy Center Honors. He received two Academy Awards, including the 1961 Academy Award for Best Director with Robert Wise for West Side Story and a special Academy Honorary Award for his choreographic achievements on film.\nA documentary about Robbins's life and work, Something to Dance About, featuring excerpts from his journals, archival performance and rehearsal footage, and interviews with Robbins and his colleagues, premiered on PBS in 2009 and won both an Emmy and a Peabody Award the same year.\n\n", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T15:30:26.726346+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2373, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerome_Robbins"}], "uuid": "618c633c-c8a0-467d-a160-b002f908a85d", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "21778", "external_references": [{"id": 10169, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q353019"}, {"id": 10170, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "9993598"}, {"id": 10171, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n85173002"}, {"id": 10172, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n85173002"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-05T21:22:27.583609+10:00"}, {"id": 76683, "name": "Jim Monro", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2649039, "title": "The World Is Watching", "work_id": 80672, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T17:54:43.771671+10: